    • Method Detail

      • find

        private int find​(Account account)
        Searches for an account in the database.
        Parameters:
        account - The account to search for.
        Returns:
        Index of an account with the same holder and type in the accounts array, -1 if account does not exist.

      • grow

        private void grow()
        Increases the length of the accounts Array by four when the array is filled.

      • checkingConflict

        private boolean checkingConflict​(Checking account)
        Determines whether there is already a checking account with the same patient in the database.
        Parameters:
        account - The account we are checking if there is a duplicate of.
        Returns:
        true if the account already exists in the database, false if not.

      • reopen

        public boolean reopen​(Account account)
        Reopens a closed account.
        Parameters:
        account - An account with the same type and holder as the one to be reopened.
        Returns:
        false if the account is not in the database or if it's already open, true otherwise.

      • open

        public boolean open​(Account account)
        Adds an account to the database if one with the same holder and type does not already exist.
        Parameters:
        account - The account to add to the database.
        Returns:
        true if the account was successfully added to the database, false if not.

      • close

        public boolean close​(Account account)
        Closes an account, if it exists in the database.
        Parameters:
        account - The account to close.
        Returns:
        true if the close was successful, false if the account is already closed.

      • isThere

        public boolean isThere​(Account account)
        Determines whether or not an account is in the database.
        Parameters:
        account - The account to search for.
        Returns:
        true if an Account with the same holder and type in database, false if not.

      • deposit

        public void deposit​(Account account)
        Adds money into an account.
        Parameters:
        account - The account to deposit into, with account.balance being the amount.

      • withdraw

        public boolean withdraw​(Account account)
        Takes money from an account, if it has enough money.
        Parameters:
        account - The account to withdraw from, with account.balance being the amount.
        Returns:
        false if insufficient funds, true otherwise.

      • print

        public java.lang.String print()
        Outputs info about all the accounts in the system as a string. Prints in whatever order they may be in.
        Returns:
        A string representation of all the accounts in the database.

      • printFeeAndInterest

        public java.lang.String printFeeAndInterest()
        Outputs the same info as the print() method plus the monthly interest and fee for each account in the system. Outputs in whatever order they may be in.
        Returns:
        A string representation of all the accounts in the database with monthly interest and fee included.

      • printByAccountType

        public java.lang.String printByAccountType()
        Sorts the accounts in the system by account type and outputs them as a string. If two accounts are the same type, it does not matter which order they are in.
        Returns:
        A string representation of all the accounts in the database sorted by account type.

      • update

        public java.lang.String update()
        Updates each of the account based on what they would be the next month and prints them to the console.
        Returns:
        A string representation of all the accounts in the database with next months's balances.

      • swap

        private void swap​(int a,
                  int b)
        Swaps elements a and b in the accounts array. For use with the printByAccountType() method.
        Parameters:
        a - First element to be swapped.
        b - Second element to be swapped.
